  <thing id="spS2ArcaM0" name="Arcane Mark" description="This spell allows you to inscribe your personal rune or mark, which can consist of no more than six characters. The writing can be visible or invisible. An {i}arcane mark{/i} spell enables you to etch the rune upon any substance without harm to the material upon which it is placed. If an invisible mark is made, a {i}detect magic{/i} spell causes it to glow and be visible, though not necessarily understandable.{br}{br}{i}See invisibility, true seeing{/i}, a {i}gem of seeing{/i}, or a {i}robe of eyes{/i} likewise allows the user to see an invisible {i}arcane mark.{/i} A {i}read magic{/i} spell reveals the words, if any. The mark cannot be dispelled, but it can be removed by the caster or by an {i}erase{/i} spell.{br}{br}If an {i}arcane mark{/i} is placed on a living being, the effect gradually fades in about a month.{br}{br}{i}Arcane mark{/i} must be cast on an object prior to casting {i}instant summons{/i} on the same object (see that spell description for details)." compset="Spell" summary="Inscribes a personal rune on an object or creature (visible or invisible).">
